  {
    "client_msg_id": "375e2f10-7e5c-466c-b1c6-8634b11f6c1d",
    "type": "message",
    "text": "At a small company I find myself using more open source code than at a large company. Docs are not always complete. In sourcegraph I can right click on a library function and “find all references” to it across all of GitHub to see examples of how to use it. Really helps in closing the gap!",
